<div id="pf3a" class="pf w3 h4" data-page-no="3a"><div class="pc pc3a w3 h4"><div class="t m112 xb0 h1d y272 ff1 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m1bd x78 h1d y7b2 ff1 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How did Moses similarly address God? Psalm 90:2. &apos; </div><div class="t m114 x47 h1d y7b3 ff1 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m253 x78 h1d y7b3 ff1 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Summarize how the psalmist speaks of God as Judge in Psalm 50:1-6. </div><div class="t m478 x47 h1d y5d ff1 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m237 x78 h1d y7b4 ff1 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How did Moses describe God to the children of Israel? Deut. 4:24. </div><div class="t m478 x47 h1d y7b5 ff1 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m3d x78 h1d y19a ff1 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What does fire issuing from God do? Psalm 97:3. </div><div class="t m447 x56 h1d y7b6 ff1 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ILLUMINATION: </div><div class="t mef x66 h1c y19e ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;Daniel is shown the final judgment in both its phases, in-</div><div class="t m3b7 x56 h1c y7b7 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">vestigative and executive. . . . The investigation is not conducted for the infor-</div><div class="t m29f x56 h1c y7b8 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">mation of God or of Christ, but for the information of the universe at large—that </div><div class="t m191 x56 h1c y1a1 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God may be vindicated in accepting some and rejecting others.&quot;—SDA </div><div class="t m3f4 x5e h1c y7b9 ff7 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Bible </div><div class="t m1e9 x56 h1c y7ba ff7 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Commentary, </div><div class="t m479 xd0 h1c y7ba ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">vol. 4, p. 828. </div><div class="t m193 x47 h1c y7bb ff7 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;The judgment was set.&quot; </div><div class="t m18d x3a h1c y7bc ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The words are simple, but the implications are tre-</div><div class="t m11f x56 h1c y7bd ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">mendous! The fate of every individual will be decided forever. </div><div class="t m47a x47 h1c y7be ff7 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;The books were opened.&quot; </div><div class="t m47b x97 h1c y7be ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Bible refers to a number of &quot;books&quot; of </div><div class="t m13f x56 h1c y7bf ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">records. </div><div class="t m115 x56 h1d y751 ff1 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SEARCH AND LEARN: Read the following texts and list the names of the </div><div class="t mc3 x56 h1d y7c0 ff1 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">books indicated: </div><div class="t m3e5 xb0 h1c y753 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ps. 69:28 </div><div class="t m141 x70 h1c y7c1 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m142 xd1 h1c y7c1 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m247 xb0 h1c y756 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Mal. 3:16 </div><div class="t m141 x70 h1c y756 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m142 xd1 h1c y756 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m47c xb0 h1c y13c ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Phil 4</div><div class="t m146 xc5 h1c y77f ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">.</div><div class="t m3ec xd2 h1c y77f ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3 </div><div class="t m141 x4f h1c y77f ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m142 xd1 h1c y77f ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m47d xb0 h1c y6f3 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Rev 3</div><div class="t m146 x36 h1c y781 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">.</div><div class="t mf1 xc5 h1c y781 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5 </div><div class="t m141 x45 h1c y781 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m142 xd1 h1c y781 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m47e xb0 h1c y6f5 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Rev. 20:12 </div><div class="t m141 xcf h1c y6f5 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m142 xd1 h1c y6f5 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m198 xb0 h1c y7c2 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The records are kept so that anyone in the universe who might challenge God&apos;s </div><div class="t m278 x56 h1c y6f6 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">justice can have access to the facts involved. </div><div class="t m1b0 x25 h1d y786 ff1 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What is one outcome of the judgment? Dan. 7:11. </div><div class="t m12c xb0 h1c y6f8 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">As a result of the judgment the persecuting beast and the blasphemous horn </div><div class="t m2b4 x56 h1c y7c3 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">will be destroyed. God is the source of life, but the wages of sin and rebellion is </div><div class="t m151 x53 h1c y7c4 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">death. Note how thorough the destruction will be: (I) The beast is slain, and the </div><div class="t m13e x53 h1c y7c5 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">horn with it—it can no longer be active, (2) the body is destroyed—there is no </div><div class="t m1e5 x53 h1c y249 ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">possibility of its reappearance, and (3) the body is given to the burning flame—</div><div class="t m151 x53 h1c y24a ff4 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">there is no possibility of contamination. </div><div class="t m2f5 x53 h1d y7c6 ff1 fs15 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">58 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
